    "id": "https://uofa.net/morrison/decision/dr-cou1-accepted-2026",
    "type": "DecisionRecord",
    "actor": "https://uofa.net/morrison/actor/lead-credibility-assessor",
    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "All seven assessed credibility factors meet or exceed required levels for MRL 2. Six factors appropriately scoped out per ASME V&V 40-2018 Table 3 guidance for MRL 2 Class II device. NIH predictions within 14.3% of bench measurements across the full CPB operating envelope. GCI of 2.8% demonstrates adequate mesh convergence. The CFD model is accepted as sufficiently credible to support identification of worst-case hemolysis operating conditions for the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump in CPB application. Decision: Accepted.",
